HEADWORD: Mandator
<hw>Man*da"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A director; one who gives a mandate or order.</def>
<rj><au>Ayliffe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Rom. Law)</fld> <def>The person who employs another
to perform a mandate.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mandatory</ent>⟦br⟧
